

---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="impermanence">
  <Article
    title="impermanence"
    section="death"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      impermanence is the fact that all things change, pass, and do not remain
      fixed. nothing holds its form indefinitely.
    </p>

    <p>
      what appears stable is only temporarily arranged. over time, structures
      shift, dissolve, or transform into something else.
    </p>

    <p>
      to see impermanence clearly is to recognize that loss and change are not
      exceptions—they are the rule.
    </p>

    <h2>change</h2>

    <p>
      everything moves. even what seems still is in process. relationships,
      identities, bodies, and environments all undergo continuous alteration.
    </p>

    <p>
      resisting this movement often creates tension, while recognizing it can
      bring a different kind of clarity.
    </p>

    <h2>passing</h2>

    <p>
      moments do not stay. experiences arise and fade. what is present now will
      not be present in the same way again.
    </p>

    <p>
      this can be unsettling, but it also gives weight to what exists. value
      emerges from transience.
    </p>

    <h2>relation to death</h2>

    <p>
      death is the most complete form of impermanence, but impermanence is
      already present long before death occurs.
    </p>

    <p>
      to understand impermanence is to begin understanding death without needing
      to wait for its final form.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death">back to death index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death/afterlife">continue to: afterlife</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/death/dance-of-death">dance of death</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>